WEBVTT

00:15.708 --> 00:18.500
(ominous music)

00:48.083 --> 00:49.208
- Thanks.

00:50.041 --> 00:51.750
Thanks for waiting.

00:54.333 --> 00:57.583
(car faintly honks)

01:09.916 --> 01:15.208
My therapist thinks that I
should stop talking to you.

01:19.291 --> 01:23.000
Which is confusing because she's the one

01:23.000 --> 01:26.125
who suggested I start talking
to you in the first place.

01:34.000 --> 01:36.583
She thinks that I can't move on.

01:45.250 --> 01:46.333
I need you.

01:48.916 --> 01:50.500
And I know that you need me.

01:55.000 --> 01:55.875
So...

01:59.750 --> 02:02.416
I'm just gonna have to
find another therapist.

02:04.916 --> 02:07.416
(car beeps)

02:12.666 --> 02:13.583
Ready?

02:21.125 --> 02:24.041
Um, he was apparently dating
some girl at the time who,

02:24.166 --> 02:27.125
whenever they would get in
an argument, she'd be like,

02:27.250 --> 02:30.208
"Well, you've never even seen Casablanca"

02:30.375 --> 02:32.416
As if that was some sort
of like a pre-requisite

02:32.583 --> 02:34.291
for being in a relationship.

02:35.125 --> 02:36.291
And I was just there that day

02:36.416 --> 02:37.583
because I had family in town

02:37.750 --> 02:40.250
and I needed to escape for a few hours.

02:42.250 --> 02:43.541
But every time we would get in a fight

02:43.666 --> 02:46.083
he would just look at me and go,

02:46.208 --> 02:47.791
"Here's looking at you, kid."

02:51.958 --> 02:55.375
(calming choral music)

02:57.041 --> 02:58.916
- [Emory] And listen, I know
you haven't felt up to it,

02:59.041 --> 03:02.583
but it is so important that
you keep your audience engaged.

03:02.708 --> 03:04.125
They're worried about you.

03:04.250 --> 03:06.458
You need to share your process.

03:06.583 --> 03:07.833
Remember who you are.

03:07.958 --> 03:08.666
- [Faye] Mhm.

03:08.666 --> 03:10.208
- [Emory] You're Faye fuckin' Ryan.

03:10.333 --> 03:13.125
Say it with me, you invented the new TLC.

03:13.250 --> 03:14.500
TL-

03:14.625 --> 03:15.458
- TLSC.

03:15.625 --> 03:16.541
- [Emory] Tender-

03:16.666 --> 03:18.333
- Tender Love and Self Care.

03:18.458 --> 03:19.708
(Faye chuckles)

03:19.833 --> 03:23.875
T-L-S-C.

03:25.000 --> 03:25.875
(Faye laughs)

03:26.000 --> 03:27.291
- [Emory] I hate to do this to you.

03:27.416 --> 03:28.875
You know we all love
you here at Lighthouse,

03:29.000 --> 03:31.500
and we really want to
continue publishing your work.

03:31.625 --> 03:34.458
But sweetie, if you can't
get me a first draft

03:34.583 --> 03:37.125
or at least the first three chapters

03:37.250 --> 03:38.750
by the end of the month,

03:38.916 --> 03:41.541
then I'm afraid we're
gonna have to drop you.

03:42.333 --> 03:44.500
- Wow, okay.

03:46.250 --> 03:48.291
I thought I had 'til March.

03:48.916 --> 03:50.750
- [Emory] I know what we should do.

03:50.875 --> 03:51.625
I have a plan.

03:51.750 --> 03:53.041
Look, I have a family cabin

03:53.166 --> 03:54.500
that we never use this time of year,

03:54.666 --> 03:56.458
it's in Louisiana, on the bayou.

03:56.583 --> 03:58.250
It has everything you need.

03:58.375 --> 03:59.875
I'll make sure it's stocked for a week.

04:00.000 --> 04:01.000
What do you say?

04:01.125 --> 04:02.916
Faye, you need to get out of town!

04:03.625 --> 04:05.208
- I used to love driving.

04:05.375 --> 04:09.875
Every Saturday morning, when
Jacob and I first got married,

04:10.041 --> 04:11.083
we would go golfing,

04:11.208 --> 04:13.875
and I would just take a drive.

04:14.000 --> 04:16.166
It honestly didn't even
matter where I was going,

04:16.291 --> 04:18.041
I could be aimless.

04:18.166 --> 04:19.333
I would roll down the windows

04:19.458 --> 04:21.958
and blare my favorite music

04:22.083 --> 04:25.916
that Jacob thought was
obnoxious, but that I loved.

04:27.916 --> 04:29.666
I would stop at a fast food restaurant

04:29.833 --> 04:33.416
and get french fries and just drive.

04:36.041 --> 04:36.916
I loved it.

04:46.875 --> 04:48.500
Now I hate it.

04:48.625 --> 04:51.458
(Faye vomits)

