1:19:01.416 --> 1:19:05.250
The cycle never ends,
but it's all important.

1:19:05.375 --> 1:19:06.500
It all belongs.

1:19:07.333 --> 1:19:12.541
The wins, the losses,
the fear, the laughter,

1:19:13.208 --> 1:19:15.666
the pain, the heartbreak.

1:19:15.791 --> 1:19:19.458
I've spent the last 6 months
talking to my dead husband,

1:19:19.583 --> 1:19:23.833
pretending he was still
alive, like nothing happened.

1:19:25.625 --> 1:19:27.125
But something did happen.

1:19:28.625 --> 1:19:29.958
A tragedy happened.

1:19:35.166 --> 1:19:37.291
The kind of story I've read
too many times to count,

1:19:37.416 --> 1:19:40.083
but not one I could accept as my own.

1:19:40.916 --> 1:19:42.041
I didn't want to heal,

1:19:42.708 --> 1:19:45.291
because healing would mean
that I had to acknowledge

1:19:45.416 --> 1:19:46.375
that I was broken.

1:19:47.166 --> 1:19:48.541
And when something heals,

1:19:48.708 --> 1:19:51.000
it doesn't mean it goes
back to its original state.

1:19:52.041 --> 1:19:53.916
Jacob is never coming back.

1:19:55.750 --> 1:19:57.791
My life will never be the same.

1:19:58.625 --> 1:20:00.916
Grief is terrifying.

1:20:06.333 --> 1:20:09.250
And it's never been
defeated by a one man army.

1:20:14.000 --> 1:20:16.500
But, what if it's not
supposed to be a fight?"

1:20:24.583 --> 1:20:25.458
That's it.

1:20:27.625 --> 1:20:28.916
Are we...

1:20:29.041 --> 1:20:30.250
Are we done?

1:20:33.041 --> 1:20:34.541
Okay, thank you.

